<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5703&amp;p=52041#p52041"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[how to save/load a game?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5703&amp;p=52041#p52041"><![CDATA[
The iNES header has a bit for "battery". If this is turned on, you save the game by writing out the emulated PRG RAM to a file every few seconds. Later, when the user plays the same ROM again, read the file back into PRG RAM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Nov 04, 2009 8:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
