<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5703&amp;p=52032#p52032"><![CDATA[
Yeah, we need more detail, but since this is the NESemdev forum, we can at least assume you're writing an emulator.<br /><br />If you're talking about save states, you need to, well, save the state of the emulator in a way that can be retrieved later. This means you have to save all CPU registers, all of RAM, VRAM, etc, so that later the emulator can reload all that stuff and resume it's previous state.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Nov 04, 2009 7:39 am</p><hr />
